WEBVTT

1
00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:50.149
<i>- Is it a girl?
- Yes.</i>

2
00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:51.872
<i>Show me its arm.</i>

3
00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:54.719
<i>- She bears the mark.
- No!</i>

4
00:00:57.320 --> 00:01:00.676
The omen is true.
I must tell my mother.

5
00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:04.991
<i>- Help me!
- I can't.</i>

6
00:01:05.120 --> 00:01:07.759
<i>They're going to kill her.</i>

7
00:01:11.520 --> 00:01:15.274
<i>Please! Please!</i>

8
00:01:15.400 --> 00:01:19.712
<i>Oh. thank you. Ethna. Thank you.</i>

9
00:01:27.920 --> 00:01:30.309
<i>Stand aside for Queen Bavmorda!</i>

10
00:01:53.760 --> 00:01:56.069
You cannot stop the prophecy!

11
00:01:56.200 --> 00:01:58.953
This child will have no power over me.
Start the ritual.

12
00:01:59.080 --> 00:02:03.676
- No. No!
- Where's the baby?

13
00:02:03.800 --> 00:02:06.075
- The midwife.
- Find that baby. Sorsha.

14
00:02:06.200 --> 00:02:09.397
Use the dogs.
Bring her back to me alive!

15
00:02:09.520 --> 00:02:11.511
Your reign of terror
is at an end!

16
00:02:11.640 --> 00:02:13.596
She will come back.
and she will finish you!

17
00:02:13.720 --> 00:02:17.076
<i>- Silence. wench. - My baby
will finish you! - Kill her.</i>

18
00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:37.837
Dada! Dada!

19
00:05:41.120 --> 00:05:44.192
<i>- Dada! Dada!
- Whoa! Whoa!</i>

20
00:05:45.520 --> 00:05:48.557
Dada! Dada!
We found something in the river.

21
00:05:48.680 --> 00:05:50.477
I can't run off and play
with you now. Ranon.

22
00:05:50.600 --> 00:05:52.670
- I've got work to do.
- You gotta come. Hurry!

23
00:05:57.600 --> 00:05:59.909
Come on.

24
00:06:02.280 --> 00:06:05.158
Don't go near it.
We don't know where it's been.

25
00:06:05.280 --> 00:06:07.999
But. Dada. it's a baby.

26
00:06:08.120 --> 00:06:12.671
- It's not like us.
- No. It's not a Nelwyn.

27
00:06:12.800 --> 00:06:16.156
<i>- It looks like a Daikini baby.
- What's a Daikini?</i>

28
00:06:16.280 --> 00:06:18.475
Daikinis are big.

29
00:06:18.600 --> 00:06:21.558
Giants who live far away.

30
00:06:21.680 --> 00:06:23.830
Oh. she's so cute.

31
00:06:23.960 --> 00:06:27.748
- Can't we keep it. Dada?
- No!

32
00:06:28.160 --> 00:06:32.836
We'll push it downstream and forget
we ever saw it. Come on.

33
00:06:32.960 --> 00:06:34.757
<i>Ufgood! Willow Ufgood!</i>

34
00:06:34.880 --> 00:06:38.839
Shhh! It's the prefect.
That's all I need.

35
00:06:38.960 --> 00:06:42.157
Keep it quiet.
Don't touch it.

36
00:06:43.760 --> 00:06:47.355
<i>Mr Burglekutt. my husband
hasn't stolen anything!</i>

37
00:06:47.480 --> 00:06:49.277
Baaa!

38
00:06:52.680 --> 00:06:55.990
<i>Ufgood. you still haven't paid
your debts to me.</i>

39
00:06:56.120 --> 00:06:57.997
Where did you get these seeds?

40
00:06:58.120 --> 00:07:00.680
Well. maybe I used magic.

41
00:07:00.800 --> 00:07:04.554
You're no sorcerer. Ufgood.
You're a clown.

42
00:07:04.680 --> 00:07:08.036
I sell the planting seeds around here.
Now tell me where you got them.

43
00:07:08.160 --> 00:07:11.436
My family's been gathering them
in the forest since last fall.

44
00:07:11.560 --> 00:07:14.393
<i>There's no law against that.</i>

45
00:07:14.520 --> 00:07:17.796
Willow. you didn't leave them
alone by the river?

46
00:07:19.560 --> 00:07:21.755
Magic?
You'll need magic...

47
00:07:21.880 --> 00:07:23.996
if you expect to get your planting
done before the rains start.

48
00:07:26.080 --> 00:07:27.877
I will have this land. Ufgood.

49
00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:31.356
And you're gonna end up
working in the mines.

50
00:07:33.520 --> 00:07:36.956
Baaa-

51
00:07:40.080 --> 00:07:42.913
Oh. you're lovely.

52
00:07:43.040 --> 00:07:44.917
Yes. you are.

53
00:07:45.040 --> 00:07:46.473
Kiaya!

54
00:07:46.600 --> 00:07:49.239
Oh. Willow!

55
00:07:49.360 --> 00:07:54.036
- Good girl. Good girl.
- Under no condition whatsoever...

56
00:07:54.160 --> 00:07:56.720
is anyone in this family
to fall in love with that baby.

57
00:07:56.840 --> 00:08:01.311
Yes. you are. Come on. Mims.
Come on. Come on.

58
00:08:01.440 --> 00:08:03.351
There we are. Come on.

59
00:08:03.480 --> 00:08:05.948
Hey. I will not be ignored!

60
00:08:06.080 --> 00:08:09.595
Mims? Ranon?

61
00:08:20.160 --> 00:08:22.116
<i>You're gonna be all clean.</i>

62
00:08:28.600 --> 00:08:31.717
Willow. do you think we should
take her to the village council?

63
00:08:31.840 --> 00:08:34.274
No. No.
They'll think it's a bad omen.

64
00:08:34.400 --> 00:08:37.073
There'll be a flood or a drought.
and everyone will blame me for it.

65
00:08:37.200 --> 00:08:39.919
"Willow Ufgood brought around
that Daikini. didn't he?"

66
00:08:40.040 --> 00:08:42.873
<i>"That's right. And he's that
lousy farmer too. Let's get him!"</i>

67
00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:46.879
- Willow. calm down.
- Calm down?

68
00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:48.911
Kiaya. tomorrow's my big day.

69
00:08:49.040 --> 00:08:52.555
<i>Love. the High Aldwin hasn't
picked a new apprentice in years.</i>

70
00:08:52.680 --> 00:08:55.717
Tomorrow's gonna be different.
I just know he's gonna pick me.

71
00:08:58.480 --> 00:09:01.916
- Here. Hold her.
- Hey. no. I don't want her. Kiaya.

72
00:09:02.040 --> 00:09:04.679
- Hold her while I get some milk.
- Oh. no. no. Oh.

73
00:09:12.040 --> 00:09:15.271
Dada. she likes you.

74
00:09:22.960 --> 00:09:26.191
<i>Bye.</i>

75
00:09:26.320 --> 00:09:29.995
Come on. kids. Let's go.

76
00:09:35.800 --> 00:09:39.236
<i>I will now magically join the rings!</i>

77
00:10:00.320 --> 00:10:02.754
Whoa-ah!

78
00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:09.670
Thank you. son.

79
00:10:09.800 --> 00:10:14.555
If you're easily shocked.
please turn away.

80
00:10:29.200 --> 00:10:31.236
Give me a ripe one. Good.

81
00:10:37.320 --> 00:10:41.598
And now. for my final amazing feat.

82
00:10:41.720 --> 00:10:46.271
I will make this entire pig disappear!

83
00:10:54.080 --> 00:10:58.949
- Mims. see?
- Please. watch very closely.

84
00:10:59.080 --> 00:11:04.359
<i>Wuppity bairn. deru. deru!</i>

85
00:11:06.640 --> 00:11:08.870
- Well-
- What happened to your pig?

86
00:11:11.520 --> 00:11:14.353
No!
Hey. come here. you!

87
00:11:18.720 --> 00:11:21.871
I seen enough.

88
00:11:36.480 --> 00:11:39.552
Attention!
The High Aldwin...

89
00:11:39.680 --> 00:11:42.433
<i>- will now make his choice for his new apprentice!
- You'll be all right.</i>

90
00:11:42.560 --> 00:11:45.836
Bring forth the hopefuls.

91
00:11:45.960 --> 00:11:48.190
- Good luck.
- Good luck. Dada.

92
00:11:48.320 --> 00:11:51.869
Willow Ufgood. a hopeful?
How did he get picked?

93
00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:54.355
Is this a joke?

94
00:11:54.480 --> 00:11:58.712
<i>Willow?</i>

95
00:12:01.000 --> 00:12:06.279
Magic is the bloodstream
of the universe!

96
00:12:06.400 --> 00:12:10.712
Forget all you know...
or think you know.

97
00:12:10.840 --> 00:12:14.628
All that you require
is your intuition.

98
00:12:14.760 --> 00:12:18.673
Now. the power
to control the world...

99
00:12:18.800 --> 00:12:21.917
is in which finger?

100
00:13:03.360 --> 00:13:07.672
No apprentice this year!

101
00:13:27.280 --> 00:13:30.477
<i>- Where's Mims?
- I don't know. She was right here!</i>

102
00:13:30.600 --> 00:13:33.319
Take Ranon in there. quick!

103
00:13:40.960 --> 00:13:43.758
Mims!

104
00:13:45.080 --> 00:13:47.116
Mims!

105
00:13:55.080 --> 00:13:59.596
- Mims!
- Dada-

106
00:14:00.920 --> 00:14:03.753
I'm scared. Dada!

107
00:14:13.720 --> 00:14:16.154
Come on!

108
00:14:33.160 --> 00:14:35.594
Vohnkar!

109
00:14:45.120 --> 00:14:47.873
- Check to make sure.
- It's dead!

110
00:14:50.160 --> 00:14:51.832
Dada! Dada!

111
00:14:55.080 --> 00:14:57.196
It was looking
for somebody's baby!

112
00:15:00.120 --> 00:15:03.669
- Mommy.
- Kiaya!

113
00:15:10.880 --> 00:15:14.031
Kiaya!
Kiaya!

114
00:15:14.160 --> 00:15:16.993
I'm here.

115
00:15:20.960 --> 00:15:24.396
Oh. Kiaya.

116
00:15:24.520 --> 00:15:26.556
We can't keep the baby. Kiaya.

117
00:15:26.680 --> 00:15:29.319
We have to take her
to the village council.

118
00:15:42.360 --> 00:15:47.036
Silence! One beast we can kill.
but there may be more.

119
00:15:47.160 --> 00:15:49.390
<i>And you can be assured
that they won't give up...</i>

120
00:15:49.520 --> 00:15:51.351
<i>until they find what
they're looking for!</i>

121
00:15:51.480 --> 00:15:54.552
<i>- It's a sign!
- Who's to blame for this?</i>

122
00:15:54.680 --> 00:15:56.989
<i>We must find the culprit
and throw him in the pit!</i>

123
00:15:57.120 --> 00:16:01.989
<i>In the pit! In the pit!</i>

124
00:16:02.120 --> 00:16:04.111
<i>In the pit! In the pit!</i>

125
00:16:04.240 --> 00:16:07.357
<i>- In the pit! In the pit!
- Willow.</i>

126
00:16:07.480 --> 00:16:11.598
<i>Willow Ufgood.</i>

127
00:16:11.720 --> 00:16:14.029
Come forward.

128
00:16:19.480 --> 00:16:24.474
My children found this baby
alone by the river. High Aldwin.

129
00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:31.991
A Daikini child.

130
00:16:32.120 --> 00:16:35.192
That's what the beasts want.
Let's give it back to them!

131
00:16:35.320 --> 00:16:36.309
Yeah!

132
00:16:36.440 --> 00:16:39.512
- They'll kill her! You can't!
- It isn't one of us.

133
00:16:39.640 --> 00:16:42.154
This child is special!

134
00:16:42.280 --> 00:16:46.353
This child must be taken beyond
the boundaries of our village.

135
00:16:46.480 --> 00:16:49.358
All the way across
the great river...

136
00:16:49.480 --> 00:16:51.436
to the Daikini crossroads.

137
00:16:51.560 --> 00:16:55.997
<i>- Well. who'll do that?
- It seems only fair...</i>

138
00:16:56.120 --> 00:16:59.317
that the man to take
this baby to the crossroads...

139
00:16:59.440 --> 00:17:02.159
be the very man who
plucked it out of the river.

140
00:17:03.800 --> 00:17:06.234
I nominate Willow Ufgood.

141
00:17:06.360 --> 00:17:08.749
No!

142
00:17:08.880 --> 00:17:12.156
I will consult the bones!

143
00:17:19.840 --> 00:17:24.595
<i>The bones tell me... nothing.</i>

144
00:17:26.200 --> 00:17:29.875
Do you have any love
for this child?

145
00:17:38.040 --> 00:17:42.318
Yes. Yes. I do.

146
00:17:42.440 --> 00:17:46.592
The bones have spoken!

147
00:17:46.720 --> 00:17:50.474
Willow Ufgood. the safety
of this village depends upon you.

148
00:17:50.600 --> 00:17:54.479
- Praise the bones!
- Praise the bones!

149
00:17:54.600 --> 00:17:56.955
<i>But you will need help.</i>

150
00:17:57.080 --> 00:18:02.074
<i>Who has the courage to protect
our brave fellow on his journey?</i>

151
00:18:04.160 --> 00:18:08.039
<i>- I'll go with him.
- Ah. Meegosh.</i>

152
00:18:08.160 --> 00:18:11.277
- Excellent choice.
- I'll go!

153
00:18:11.400 --> 00:18:13.709
Vohnkar! Vohnkar!

154
00:18:13.840 --> 00:18:16.354
No! Not Vohnkar!
He's the best warrior in the village!

155
00:18:16.480 --> 00:18:19.438
<i>We need him here!
Vohnkar. step back!</i>

156
00:18:27.240 --> 00:18:29.674
All this expedition needs
is a leader.

157
00:18:29.800 --> 00:18:32.951
<i>And according to the bones...</i>

158
00:18:33.080 --> 00:18:35.913
<i>that leader is...</i>

159
00:18:36.040 --> 00:18:38.713
<i>you. Burglekutt!</i>

160
00:18:38.840 --> 00:18:41.308
Vohnkar!

161
00:18:42.280 --> 00:18:46.159
- What's your problem. son?
- How do you mean?

162
00:18:46.880 --> 00:18:51.317
When I held up my fingers.
what was your first impulse?

163
00:18:51.440 --> 00:18:55.115
- Well. it was stupid.
- Just tell me.

164
00:18:55.240 --> 00:18:59.472
- To pick my own finger.
- Aha! That was the correct answer.

165
00:18:59.600 --> 00:19:04.071
You lack faith in yourself.
More than anyone in the village.

166
00:19:04.200 --> 00:19:06.668
<i>you have the potential
to be a great sorcerer.</i>

167
00:19:06.800 --> 00:19:11.316
Now. when you're out there.
listen to your own heart.

168
00:19:13.040 --> 00:19:18.068
- These will protect you. They're magic!
- Acorns?

169
00:19:18.200 --> 00:19:21.909
Anything you throw them at
turns to stone.

170
00:19:24.960 --> 00:19:28.032
<i>You have much to learn.
young Ufgood.</i>

171
00:19:40.480 --> 00:19:44.712
- Are you scared. Dada?
- No!

172
00:19:44.840 --> 00:19:46.796
Even with fairies in the woods...

173
00:19:46.920 --> 00:19:48.797
that'll put you to sleep
for a hundred years?

174
00:19:50.360 --> 00:19:52.794
- Doesn't bother me.
- Brownies?

175
00:19:52.920 --> 00:19:55.673
<i>- Dragons?
- Trolls?</i>

176
00:19:55.800 --> 00:19:59.076
Trolls that'll skin you alive
and take your face off?

177
00:19:59.200 --> 00:20:02.590
Ranon!
You know I hate trolls.

178
00:20:02.720 --> 00:20:05.678
I can be your guard
and carry your spear.

179
00:20:05.800 --> 00:20:07.313
Me too. Me too. Dada.

180
00:20:08.840 --> 00:20:13.834
What a lucky father I am. I wish
I could take you bobbins with me.

181
00:20:16.920 --> 00:20:19.309
Goodbye. Dada.

182
00:20:21.320 --> 00:20:23.515
Go play!
Go on.

183
00:20:28.960 --> 00:20:31.554
We've never been apart.

184
00:20:34.280 --> 00:20:36.430
I miss you already.

185
00:20:37.840 --> 00:20:41.071
Don't worry. Kiaya.
I'll be fine.

186
00:20:41.200 --> 00:20:42.918
I'll be back
before you know it.

187
00:20:45.200 --> 00:20:47.760
Well. remember
to keep her warm.

188
00:20:49.760 --> 00:20:52.274
And... here.

189
00:20:54.440 --> 00:20:57.079
This will bring you luck.

190
00:21:09.760 --> 00:21:11.876
Good brave people!

191
00:21:13.760 --> 00:21:16.320
The outer world is
no place for a Nelwyn.

192
00:21:16.440 --> 00:21:18.954
Give the baby
to the first Daikini you see.

193
00:21:19.080 --> 00:21:21.116
then hurry home.

194
00:21:24.360 --> 00:21:27.750
<i>Tuatha...
lokwathrak... tuatha!</i>

195
00:21:27.880 --> 00:21:31.190
<i>Go in the direction the bird is flying!</i>

196
00:21:35.160 --> 00:21:37.799
It's going back to the village!

197
00:21:39.640 --> 00:21:41.517
Ignore the bird.
Follow the river.

198
00:21:41.640 --> 00:21:43.756
Move out!

199
00:22:06.760 --> 00:22:10.036
- Hold on. Meegosh.
- What's wrong?

200
00:22:10.160 --> 00:22:13.948
- We have to stop.
- Stop? Why?

201
00:22:14.080 --> 00:22:16.310
The baby's sick.

202
00:22:20.280 --> 00:22:23.238
She's not sick!
Let me see.

203
00:22:24.760 --> 00:22:27.752
Uhaghh!
Take her! Take her!

204
00:22:30.320 --> 00:22:33.198
She'll be fine
once she gets some rest.

205
00:22:35.600 --> 00:22:37.352
Clean me up.

206
00:22:40.600 --> 00:22:43.672
I didn't ask you
to bring me a dead nursemaid.

207
00:22:43.800 --> 00:22:47.475
- Sorsha. you're useless!
- I'm backtracking the nursemaid's trail.

208
00:22:47.600 --> 00:22:49.670
I'll find where she hid the baby.

209
00:22:51.600 --> 00:22:53.716
Ah. General Kael. at last.

210
00:22:53.840 --> 00:22:58.311
My queen. I have destroyed
the castle at Galladoorn.

211
00:22:58.440 --> 00:23:01.910
Well done. But now I have
another task for you.

212
00:23:02.040 --> 00:23:07.239
Help my daughter to find
that tiny. helpless baby...

213
00:23:07.360 --> 00:23:09.157
that continues
somehow to elude her.

214
00:23:11.120 --> 00:23:12.951
The baby of the prophecy?

215
00:23:13.080 --> 00:23:16.311
- The one that would destroy you?
- I need that baby alive.

216
00:23:16.440 --> 00:23:18.715
<i>I must perform
the ritual that will exile...</i>

217
00:23:18.840 --> 00:23:22.037
the child's spirit into oblivion.

218
00:23:22.160 --> 00:23:24.720
- Find her!
- I don't need his help. Mother.

219
00:23:24.840 --> 00:23:26.717
You'll do as I say. child.

220
00:23:33.000 --> 00:23:35.036
I read the signs.

221
00:23:35.160 --> 00:23:38.152
<i>One day. I fear.
your daughter will betray you.</i>

222
00:23:38.280 --> 00:23:42.239
I trust her loyalty
more than I trust yours.

223
00:23:57.360 --> 00:23:59.749
Move!

224
00:23:59.880 --> 00:24:01.677
It's an ambush.
Come on. Move!

225
00:24:05.880 --> 00:24:09.395
Come on!

226
00:24:18.640 --> 00:24:21.393
The Nelwyns have got the baby.
We've searched the village.

227
00:24:21.520 --> 00:24:24.318
<i>But a group of them
are on the road somewhere.</i>

228
00:24:24.440 --> 00:24:26.112
<i>They couldn't have gone far!</i>

229
00:24:26.240 --> 00:24:29.038
Widen the search
and report to Sorsha!

230
00:24:36.200 --> 00:24:38.760
Come. We'll keep to the woods.

231
00:25:15.960 --> 00:25:19.953
That's it!
It's the crossroads!

232
00:25:35.760 --> 00:25:38.479
Keep this fire high.
We don't know what's out there.

233
00:25:43.920 --> 00:25:46.150
<i>What was that?</i>

234
00:25:47.560 --> 00:25:50.199
Get the spears!

235
00:26:06.040 --> 00:26:07.837
Uhh. Uhh.

236
00:26:07.960 --> 00:26:11.589
Give me some water. peck.
or you die.

237
00:26:11.720 --> 00:26:13.995
<i>Do you understand?</i>

238
00:26:14.120 --> 00:26:15.872
- Water.
- Yeah.

239
00:26:18.000 --> 00:26:19.797
Hurry up!

240
00:26:23.760 --> 00:26:26.479
<i>Get me some water.
you measly little pecks.</i>

241
00:26:27.840 --> 00:26:29.876
It's a Daikini.
We're in luck.

242
00:26:30.000 --> 00:26:32.275
We can't give her to him!

243
00:26:32.400 --> 00:26:36.154
- Somebody put him there for a reason.
- We've got to get rid of her.

244
00:26:36.280 --> 00:26:38.714
- Those soldiers are after us.
- Shhh.

245
00:26:38.840 --> 00:26:41.479
He's looking right at us.

246
00:26:45.360 --> 00:26:47.191
We've got to give
that baby to somebody.

247
00:26:47.320 --> 00:26:49.993
I'm somebody.

248
00:26:50.120 --> 00:26:54.193
Let me out of here. I'll take care
of the baby.

249
00:26:56.080 --> 00:27:00.437
- I trust him completely.
- But he tried to strangle me.

250
00:27:00.560 --> 00:27:04.269
<i>- I want to go home!
- No. Burglekutt!</i>

251
00:27:04.400 --> 00:27:07.551
<i>- We should wait!
- Are you challenging my authority?</i>

252
00:27:07.680 --> 00:27:10.831
As far as this baby
is concerned... yes.

253
00:27:10.960 --> 00:27:13.838
<i>Don't listen to him. Burglekutt.</i>

254
00:27:15.080 --> 00:27:18.789
Fine. You stay here alone.
but we're going.

255
00:27:18.920 --> 00:27:20.990
<i>That's a bad idea.
Very bad.</i>

256
00:27:21.120 --> 00:27:24.351
<i>- Dangerous out there.
- Get the gear. men.</i>

257
00:27:24.480 --> 00:27:27.836
- Vohnkar-
- It's not his decision!

258
00:27:27.960 --> 00:27:31.669
Burglekutt. you're troll dung.

259
00:27:31.800 --> 00:27:33.358
Don't let him
talk to you that way.

260
00:27:33.480 --> 00:27:35.436
Listen here. runt.

261
00:27:35.560 --> 00:27:39.348
<i>While you're wasting time here.
your fields aren't getting planted.</i>

262
00:27:39.480 --> 00:27:43.519
- Think about it!
- Burglekutt. I'm gonna-

263
00:27:43.640 --> 00:27:46.837
You're gonna what?

264
00:27:50.640 --> 00:27:53.029
Someday. Burglekutt.
Someday.

265
00:27:53.160 --> 00:27:54.991
Vohnkar. let's go!

266
00:27:58.640 --> 00:28:01.200
Meegosh. are you coming?

267
00:28:03.400 --> 00:28:06.790
- I'm staying.
- Come on. men.

268
00:28:06.920 --> 00:28:10.879
Burglekutt. let me out of here.
I'll take care of the baby. I swear.

269
00:28:11.000 --> 00:28:13.514
<i>Just let me out of here.
Please!</i>

270
00:28:13.640 --> 00:28:16.916
Vohnkar. let me borrow that spear...
just for a minute.

271
00:28:17.040 --> 00:28:19.156
Well. at least get me some water!

272
00:28:19.280 --> 00:28:23.990
Burglekutt. don't leave me alone
with these two!

273
00:28:24.120 --> 00:28:28.636
What'll we do now. Willow?

274
00:28:28.760 --> 00:28:31.228
Well. that was really stupid. peck.

275
00:28:31.360 --> 00:28:35.911
- Don't call me a peck.
- Oh. I'm sorry... peck.

276
00:28:36.040 --> 00:28:39.589
- Peck. peck. peck. peck.
- You be careful!

277
00:28:39.720 --> 00:28:43.190
I'm a powerful sorcerer.
See this acorn?

278
00:28:44.680 --> 00:28:48.958
- I'll throw it. and turn you to stone.
- Whoo-

279
00:28:49.080 --> 00:28:50.877
I'm really scared.

280
00:28:51.040 --> 00:28:53.713
<i>No. don't! Don't!</i>

281
00:28:53.840 --> 00:28:56.479
There's a peck here
with an acorn pointed at me!

282
00:28:56.600 --> 00:28:59.114
Oh. I wouldn't want to waste it.

283
00:28:59.240 --> 00:29:02.312
Ha!
Peck. peck. peck. peck.

284
00:29:02.440 --> 00:29:04.829
<i>peck. peck. peck.
peck. peck!</i>

285
00:29:32.320 --> 00:29:34.993
<i>What was that?</i>

286
00:29:38.360 --> 00:29:41.830
Mornin'. boys.

287
00:29:41.960 --> 00:29:45.873
Rough night last night.
wasn't it?

288
00:29:46.000 --> 00:29:49.151
I don't think I introduced
myself yesterday.

289
00:29:49.280 --> 00:29:52.556
My name is Madmartigan.
and you are. uh-

290
00:29:52.680 --> 00:29:55.478
No. Meegosh.
Don't go near him.

291
00:29:55.600 --> 00:29:58.832
- He's dangerous.
- I am not.

292
00:29:58.960 --> 00:30:00.996
Good.

293
00:30:05.560 --> 00:30:07.676
Stop! Wait!

294
00:30:09.440 --> 00:30:12.034
<i>Whoa!</i>

295
00:30:17.320 --> 00:30:20.630
- What's going on?
- Smells like a battle.

296
00:30:21.720 --> 00:30:24.109
I suppose you're a warrior.

297
00:30:24.240 --> 00:30:26.549
I am the greatest swordsman
that ever lived.

298
00:30:26.680 --> 00:30:29.353
Hmph.

299
00:30:29.480 --> 00:30:32.950
Say. uh- Could I have
some of that water?

300
00:30:42.400 --> 00:30:46.871
I don't know why I try.

301
00:30:51.560 --> 00:30:54.632
I guess I am gonna die here.
Who cares?

302
00:30:54.760 --> 00:30:56.557
- Here.
- Thanks. friend. Oh!

303
00:30:56.680 --> 00:30:58.910
<i>What's that?</i>

304
00:30:59.040 --> 00:31:02.794
<i>I'd say
two or three hundred horses.</i>

305
00:31:02.920 --> 00:31:06.674
five or six wagons.
and about a thousand fools.

306
00:31:09.360 --> 00:31:12.909
- Thank you. Ohh-
- Come on. Meegosh.

307
00:31:17.120 --> 00:31:20.669
It's gonna be
all right. little bobbin.

308
00:31:26.400 --> 00:31:30.109
Everything's gonna be all right.

309
00:31:33.400 --> 00:31:36.233
- Excuse me. sir.
- Out of the way. peck!

310
00:31:38.200 --> 00:31:40.430
<i>Uh. pardon me.</i>

311
00:31:40.560 --> 00:31:42.516
Uh-

312
00:31:47.960 --> 00:31:52.954
Excuse me. sir. We found one
of your babies in our village.

313
00:31:53.080 --> 00:31:55.799
Will you please take care of her?

314
00:31:55.920 --> 00:32:00.038
We're going into battle. little ones.
Find a woman to take care of her.

315
00:32:01.560 --> 00:32:04.518
<i>They thought you were
a woman. Airk.</i>

316
00:32:04.640 --> 00:32:06.870
Well-

317
00:32:07.000 --> 00:32:09.389
Madmartigan!
What did you do this time?

318
00:32:09.520 --> 00:32:11.351
Nothing you wouldn't have done.

319
00:32:11.480 --> 00:32:13.675
<i>I always knew
you'd end up in a crow's cage.</i>

320
00:32:13.800 --> 00:32:15.518
At least I'm not
down there herding sheep.

321
00:32:15.640 --> 00:32:17.039
What are you doing this far north?

322
00:32:17.160 --> 00:32:19.958
The Nockmaar army
destroyed Galladoorn.

323
00:32:20.080 --> 00:32:21.638
The castle?

324
00:32:21.760 --> 00:32:23.671
Bavmorda's troops are
crushing everything in sight.

325
00:32:23.800 --> 00:32:25.597
Come on.
Let me out of here. Airk.

326
00:32:25.720 --> 00:32:27.790
Give me a sword.
I'll win this war for you.

327
00:32:27.920 --> 00:32:32.118
Madmartigan-
I still serve Galladoorn.

328
00:32:32.240 --> 00:32:34.071
<i>You serve no one.</i>

329
00:32:34.200 --> 00:32:36.316
Remember?

330
00:32:36.440 --> 00:32:39.477
Sit in your coffin and rot.

331
00:32:39.600 --> 00:32:42.478
Wait. Airk. You need me!

332
00:32:42.600 --> 00:32:44.875
I'll be around
long after you're dead!

333
00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:47.468
<i>When I get out of here.
I'm gonna cut your head off...</i>

334
00:32:47.600 --> 00:32:49.556
and stick it on a pig pole!

335
00:33:06.400 --> 00:33:10.916
I miss Kiaya and the bobbins.

336
00:33:15.120 --> 00:33:17.076
We're running out of food.

337
00:33:19.800 --> 00:33:21.916
Nobody's gonna
take care of that baby.

338
00:33:22.040 --> 00:33:24.759
You know why?
Nobody cares.

339
00:33:27.680 --> 00:33:29.636
Except me.

340
00:33:30.760 --> 00:33:35.117
You want to go back to your families.
I want out of this cage.

341
00:33:35.240 --> 00:33:38.994
Let me take care of that baby.
I'll look after her like she was my own.

342
00:33:39.120 --> 00:33:41.918
I believe he would. Willow.

343
00:33:42.040 --> 00:33:44.429
He doesn't know
anything about babies.

344
00:33:44.560 --> 00:33:49.509
Right. But I know
a lot of women who do.

345
00:33:49.640 --> 00:33:52.393
<i>If I had somebody in my life.</i>

346
00:33:52.520 --> 00:33:55.910
a little daughter. perhaps.

347
00:33:56.040 --> 00:33:59.077
I might have a reason
to go on living.

348
00:34:02.280 --> 00:34:04.919
You can't leave me
in here to die.

349
00:34:05.040 --> 00:34:07.918
Not when all I want
to do is protect her.

350
00:34:20.760 --> 00:34:24.435
I feel better!

351
00:34:24.560 --> 00:34:28.075
- You've done the right thing!
- Okay. All right. All right.

352
00:34:28.200 --> 00:34:32.432
- You gotta promise to feed her.
- Come to Daddy. little darlin'.

353
00:34:32.560 --> 00:34:35.597
- And keep her clean.
- Absolutely.

354
00:34:37.440 --> 00:34:39.351
<i>Hee. hee. hee!</i>

355
00:34:39.480 --> 00:34:44.110
Wheee!

356
00:34:45.280 --> 00:34:47.316
She likes me.

357
00:34:49.360 --> 00:34:51.590
Here are her changing rags.

358
00:34:51.720 --> 00:34:53.790
- And her milk bladder.
- Any milk in there?

359
00:34:53.920 --> 00:34:57.879
- It's for her!
- I wouldn't steal from a baby.

360
00:35:00.720 --> 00:35:02.995
You worry too much. peck.

361
00:35:03.120 --> 00:35:06.112
- It's Willow.
- I mean Willow.

362
00:35:07.440 --> 00:35:12.434
Now listen. boys- Willow.
You've done the right thing.

363
00:35:12.560 --> 00:35:15.677
Now I want you to get home
and bring your crop in.

364
00:35:21.600 --> 00:35:23.830
Goodbye. little one.

365
00:35:34.560 --> 00:35:36.516
Please. take good care of her.

366
00:35:38.800 --> 00:35:40.995
I give you my word of honour!

367
00:35:48.040 --> 00:35:51.191
- Meegosh. slow down!
- Oh. come on!

368
00:35:51.320 --> 00:35:55.313
If we hurry. we can be home by
tomorrow morning. We'll be heroes.

369
00:35:55.440 --> 00:35:58.750
- Do you really think so?
- Sure.

370
00:35:58.880 --> 00:36:00.996
"Look. there's Willow and Meegosh.

371
00:36:01.120 --> 00:36:03.236
The heroes have come home. "

372
00:36:03.360 --> 00:36:06.238
"Welcome back. boys.
You deserve medals!"

373
00:36:06.360 --> 00:36:10.399
Yeah. Medals.

374
00:36:10.520 --> 00:36:13.592
Meegosh-

375
00:36:15.880 --> 00:36:19.793
- Did we do the right thing?
- Absolutely.

376
00:36:19.920 --> 00:36:23.913
<i>There's nothing to worry about.</i>

377
00:36:26.920 --> 00:36:29.070
Hyah! Ha ha!

378
00:36:29.200 --> 00:36:34.149
<i>I stole the baby! I stole the baby!</i>

379
00:36:34.280 --> 00:36:37.829
- Hyah!
- That's my baby!

380
00:36:37.960 --> 00:36:39.791
<i>Stop! Wait! Come back!</i>

381
00:36:39.920 --> 00:36:42.832
Left. you stupid bird.
Left! Ha ha!

382
00:36:46.680 --> 00:36:49.114
Ow!

383
00:36:49.240 --> 00:36:52.357
Brownies!
Let's get out of here!

384
00:36:52.480 --> 00:36:55.517
- Come on. Meegosh!
- Ow!

385
00:37:01.440 --> 00:37:03.351
We'll outrun 'em!

386
00:37:07.960 --> 00:37:11.839
<i>Hey. ugly. wake up!</i>

387
00:37:11.960 --> 00:37:14.235
<i>Huh?</i>

388
00:37:14.400 --> 00:37:19.190
Stand your ground. He's our prisoner.

389
00:37:19.320 --> 00:37:21.914
Meegosh.
where's the baby?

390
00:37:22.040 --> 00:37:23.837
<i>Bring the Nelwyns to me.</i>

391
00:37:23.960 --> 00:37:25.279
All right. you heard her!

392
00:37:25.400 --> 00:37:28.949
- What's going on?
- Shut up. or I'll break your nose.

393
00:37:29.080 --> 00:37:31.310
You are mine to toy with.

394
00:37:31.440 --> 00:37:34.750
Forward!

395
00:37:34.880 --> 00:37:38.475
Gimme the rope.

396
00:37:38.600 --> 00:37:42.388
Where-
Where...

397
00:37:42.520 --> 00:37:44.636
did you get that baby?

398
00:37:44.760 --> 00:37:49.276
I stole it from a stupid Daikini.

399
00:37:49.480 --> 00:37:52.472
<i>Franjean. release the Nelwyns.</i>

400
00:37:52.600 --> 00:37:56.639
<i>- And stop pestering them.
- Uh-oh.</i>

401
00:38:00.920 --> 00:38:02.751
Yaah!

402
00:38:11.240 --> 00:38:13.196
<i>Welcome to my kingdom.</i>

403
00:38:20.840 --> 00:38:25.118
- I'm happy to meet you. Willow Ufgood.
- How do you know my name?

404
00:38:25.240 --> 00:38:28.312
Elora Danan told me.

405
00:38:28.440 --> 00:38:31.477
Elora?
Elora. Willow is here.

406
00:38:34.280 --> 00:38:39.559
- But she's just a baby.
- She's very special.

407
00:38:39.680 --> 00:38:44.754
<i>My Brownies have been searching for her
ever since we heard she was born.</i>

408
00:38:45.880 --> 00:38:49.555
Elora Danan has chosen you
to be her guardian.

409
00:38:49.680 --> 00:38:54.470
- Me?
- Yes. She likes you.

410
00:38:55.600 --> 00:39:00.310
<i>And Elora Danan knows
you have the courage to help us.</i>

411
00:39:00.440 --> 00:39:03.830
Take my wand
to the sorceress. Fin Raziel.

412
00:39:03.960 --> 00:39:07.999
She will guide you and Elora Danan
to the kingdom of Tir Asleen.

413
00:39:08.120 --> 00:39:11.032
where a good king and queen
will look after her.

414
00:39:11.160 --> 00:39:14.675
You need a warrior
for a job like this. I'm a nobody.

415
00:39:14.800 --> 00:39:17.997
Elora. you don't want me.

416
00:39:18.120 --> 00:39:21.590
Tell her.
I'm short. even for a Nelwyn.

417
00:39:25.720 --> 00:39:27.676
Hello?

418
00:39:34.080 --> 00:39:37.277
Elora Danan must survive!

419
00:39:37.400 --> 00:39:42.030
She must fulfil her destiny and bring
about the downfall of Queen Bavmorda.

420
00:39:42.160 --> 00:39:44.799
whose powers are growing
like an evil plague.

421
00:39:44.920 --> 00:39:49.072
<i>Unless she is stopped.
Bavmorda will control the lives...</i>

422
00:39:49.200 --> 00:39:53.512
<i>of your village.
your children- everyone.</i>

423
00:39:58.040 --> 00:40:01.350
<i>All creatures of good heart
need your help. Willow.</i>

424
00:40:02.680 --> 00:40:05.069
The choice is yours.

425
00:40:28.680 --> 00:40:32.150
- Hey. Meegosh. Wake up.
- Huh?

426
00:40:32.280 --> 00:40:36.273
- It's time to go home.
- Home?

427
00:40:38.800 --> 00:40:43.271
Listen. Meegosh.
Tell Kiaya I love her.

428
00:40:43.400 --> 00:40:46.597
- And I think of her every day.
- Willow-

429
00:40:46.720 --> 00:40:49.996
And tell her I'm not going to let
anything happen to the baby.

430
00:40:50.120 --> 00:40:52.588
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

431
00:40:54.200 --> 00:40:56.668
I hope so.

432
00:40:56.920 --> 00:40:58.911
Listen. be careful.

433
00:41:04.880 --> 00:41:09.032
- I know the way. Franjean.
- You always think you know the way.

434
00:41:09.160 --> 00:41:10.912
<i>I am the leader!</i>

435
00:41:11.040 --> 00:41:13.429
- How long will it take to find Raziel?
- Not long.

436
00:41:13.560 --> 00:41:16.950
She's been exiled to an island
just over those hills.

437
00:41:17.080 --> 00:41:19.992
- She's what?
- Exiled...

438
00:41:20.120 --> 00:41:23.749
by the evil Queen Bavmorda.

439
00:41:23.880 --> 00:41:26.348
Rool. you fool. He does not need
to know everything.

440
00:41:26.480 --> 00:41:28.914
- I didn't tell him everything.
- You told him enough.

441
00:41:29.040 --> 00:41:31.190
<i>- You mentioned the island. the queen.
- Wait a minute.</i>

442
00:41:31.320 --> 00:41:33.788
So?

443
00:41:33.920 --> 00:41:36.559
<i>What do you mean? What are
you saying. mysterious island?</i>

444
00:41:36.680 --> 00:41:39.148
Don't play with that wand.

445
00:41:39.280 --> 00:41:41.669
Cherlindrea told you
it holds vast powers.

446
00:41:41.800 --> 00:41:44.155
<i>Only a great sorcerer can use it.</i>

447
00:41:44.280 --> 00:41:46.840
<i>not a stupid peck like you.</i>

448
00:41:46.960 --> 00:41:49.918
- This way.
- No. No. No. I don't think so.

449
00:41:50.040 --> 00:41:52.190
- All right. then this way.
- Eh. nope.

450
00:41:52.320 --> 00:41:54.709
- This way.
- This way?

451
00:41:54.840 --> 00:41:58.355
- That's what I said.
- This way.

452
00:41:58.480 --> 00:42:01.756
- You know where you're going?
- Of course.

453
00:42:01.880 --> 00:42:04.394
With us as your guides.
no harm will befall you.

454
00:42:14.440 --> 00:42:18.353
Take it up!

455
00:42:19.880 --> 00:42:23.919
- We are not going in there!
- But Elora needs fresh milk.

456
00:42:24.040 --> 00:42:28.636
- And we are drenched.
- You are not in command. shorty. I am!

457
00:42:28.760 --> 00:42:32.196
You hear me? Whoa!

458
00:43:08.440 --> 00:43:10.715
Excuse me? Excuse me.

459
00:43:10.840 --> 00:43:13.638
Could you spare some milk
for this poor. hungry baby?

460
00:43:13.760 --> 00:43:17.878
- Get out of here. peck!
- Get outta here or we'll cook ya!

461
00:43:32.160 --> 00:43:34.390
Ooh. look at her!

462
00:43:34.520 --> 00:43:36.670
<i>I could use
a love potion on her!</i>

463
00:43:36.800 --> 00:43:40.395
Franjean! Hey! Give me that
dust of broken heart.

464
00:43:40.520 --> 00:43:42.112
Come on! Give it to me!

465
00:43:42.240 --> 00:43:45.437
It's very dangerous.
It belongs to the fairies!

466
00:43:49.480 --> 00:43:51.357
Hey. quiet!
You want to get us killed?

467
00:43:58.080 --> 00:44:01.629
<i>Oh. Rool! Always playing
with those fairy love potions.</i>

468
00:44:03.880 --> 00:44:08.749
You are so beautiful!

469
00:44:08.880 --> 00:44:12.316
<i>Your eyes! Your whiskers!</i>

470
00:44:12.440 --> 00:44:14.908
<i>- I have to kiss you!
- Rool!</i>

471
00:44:15.040 --> 00:44:16.678
That dust of broken heart!

472
00:44:31.000 --> 00:44:33.070
Beer!

473
00:44:36.080 --> 00:44:38.036
These people are crazy!
This could be bad!

474
00:44:42.480 --> 00:44:44.357
<i>Hurry! Hurry!</i>

475
00:44:44.480 --> 00:44:46.232
My husband's coming!

476
00:44:46.360 --> 00:44:48.271
If he catches you here.
he'll kill us both!

477
00:44:48.400 --> 00:44:50.868
<i>- How do I look?
- Not you!</i>

478
00:44:52.080 --> 00:44:53.877
Where the hell
did you come from?

479
00:44:54.000 --> 00:44:56.116
I knew I shouldn't
have trusted you.

480
00:44:56.240 --> 00:44:59.835
Don't I know you?
I stole the baby from you. Daikini.

481
00:44:59.960 --> 00:45:02.030
<i>- while you were taking a pee-pee!
- Cover your face!</i>

482
00:45:02.160 --> 00:45:05.596
- You are crawling with Brownies.
- I hate Brownies!

483
00:45:05.720 --> 00:45:08.359
Whoa!

484
00:45:08.480 --> 00:45:10.914
- Where is he? Where?
- Hello. dear.

485
00:45:11.040 --> 00:45:13.270
There's nobody here but
me and. uh. my. uh-

486
00:45:13.400 --> 00:45:15.630
- I'll kill him!
- ... my cousin. Hilda.

487
00:45:15.760 --> 00:45:17.876
<i>- Hilda?
- Hilda.</i>

488
00:45:18.000 --> 00:45:19.991
- Oh. Hilda!
- This is my husband. Llug.

489
00:45:20.120 --> 00:45:22.680
<i>- Mm. Big husband.
- Yes.</i>

490
00:45:22.800 --> 00:45:24.518
How do you do?

491
00:45:24.640 --> 00:45:26.870
<i>Hilda! Ooh.</i>

492
00:45:27.000 --> 00:45:28.956
Come on. girly.
Don't be shy.

493
00:45:29.080 --> 00:45:31.548
Hey! Give her back!

494
00:45:31.680 --> 00:45:33.955
- Pecks make terrible nursemaids.
- Nursemaid?

495
00:45:34.080 --> 00:45:36.799
They get too excited.

496
00:45:36.920 --> 00:45:39.354
Excuse me!
Are we having a party?

497
00:45:39.520 --> 00:45:41.397
- Huh?
- Hey. hey. hey. hey!

498
00:45:41.560 --> 00:45:45.951
Stop. please. Ooh.

499
00:45:46.080 --> 00:45:47.832
Come on.
Fight like a man!

500
00:45:47.960 --> 00:45:50.793
Want to breed?

501
00:45:50.920 --> 00:45:53.753
Tempting. but no.

502
00:45:56.640 --> 00:45:58.437
Thank you.
Time to leave.

503
00:45:58.560 --> 00:46:00.312
- Bye. Hilda!
- Take them out.

504
00:46:00.440 --> 00:46:03.432
<i>Hey! Come along!</i>

505
00:46:03.560 --> 00:46:05.994
- Careful. you lout!
- Move along!

506
00:46:06.120 --> 00:46:08.680
<i>Gather up all these babies.</i>

507
00:46:08.800 --> 00:46:10.950
<i>That baby over there.
Let me see its arm.</i>

508
00:46:14.560 --> 00:46:16.551
That's not the one.

509
00:46:20.160 --> 00:46:22.754
You! Are you the mother
of that child?

510
00:46:22.880 --> 00:46:25.314
- Yes. Yes. I am.
- Let me see it.

511
00:46:25.440 --> 00:46:26.919
No! Don't let her!

512
00:46:27.040 --> 00:46:28.393
Aah!

513
00:46:28.520 --> 00:46:31.239
I gave you an order. woman!

514
00:46:40.240 --> 00:46:43.516
You-
You're... beautiful.

515
00:46:43.640 --> 00:46:46.791
- And you're very strong.
- Thank you.

516
00:46:49.320 --> 00:46:51.675
You're no woman!

517
00:46:51.800 --> 00:46:53.518
<i>Now. honey. take it easy.</i>

518
00:46:53.640 --> 00:46:56.313
- Gentlemen.
- Not a woman?

519
00:46:56.440 --> 00:46:59.079
Meet Llug.

520
00:47:00.360 --> 00:47:02.316
- After them!
- Out of the way!

521
00:47:08.360 --> 00:47:09.475
To the horses!

522
00:47:19.680 --> 00:47:21.432
Hyah!

523
00:47:21.560 --> 00:47:25.235
Madmartigan!
Madmartigan! Wait!

524
00:47:28.640 --> 00:47:31.279
He's not a woman!

525
00:47:33.400 --> 00:47:35.550
Don't let them get away!

526
00:47:37.280 --> 00:47:40.556
Madmartigan. stop!

527
00:47:58.760 --> 00:48:01.115
Madmartigan.
I'm warning you-

528
00:48:03.160 --> 00:48:06.596
- Ow!
- Prepare to die!

529
00:48:29.120 --> 00:48:31.315
Madmartigan!
Stop!

530
00:48:46.680 --> 00:48:49.717
No... more... beer.

531
00:49:00.160 --> 00:49:02.116
Franjean. help me!

532
00:49:06.560 --> 00:49:08.357
<i>- Rool!
- Help!</i>

533
00:49:08.480 --> 00:49:11.392
Rool! Rool.

534
00:49:12.560 --> 00:49:16.155
- Rool! What are you doing?
- Help me!

535
00:49:21.320 --> 00:49:23.436
- Come on. I am.
- Pull me in.

536
00:49:23.560 --> 00:49:25.915
<i>Yeah. pull!</i>

537
00:49:51.000 --> 00:49:52.592
Whoa!

538
00:49:59.080 --> 00:50:02.470
Rool. this isn't funny!
Help me cut the rope!

539
00:50:15.160 --> 00:50:17.754
Who-oa!

540
00:50:38.400 --> 00:50:40.868
Willow. stay down!

541
00:50:44.480 --> 00:50:46.357
Whoa!

542
00:50:46.480 --> 00:50:48.550
Whoa!

543
00:50:48.680 --> 00:50:50.477
Have you gone crazy?

544
00:50:50.600 --> 00:50:52.636
<i>You can't chase around
with Elora like this.</i>

545
00:50:52.760 --> 00:50:54.990
- We're getting off!
- Hyah!

546
00:50:55.120 --> 00:50:57.588
Hold on! Hyah!

547
00:51:19.520 --> 00:51:21.795
Whoa! Whoa!

548
00:51:25.000 --> 00:51:27.150
Oh. Rool.

549
00:51:27.280 --> 00:51:29.748
Now we stop. peck.

550
00:51:30.880 --> 00:51:35.908
Stupid Daikini.
Ask him to stop the wagon.

551
00:51:36.040 --> 00:51:40.033
Madmartigan! You never. ever
drive that fast with an infant!

552
00:51:41.480 --> 00:51:43.869
I just saved that infant's life!

553
00:51:45.320 --> 00:51:47.515
Hah! Hah!

554
00:51:47.640 --> 00:51:49.437
Gather your wits. Come on.

555
00:51:49.560 --> 00:51:52.438
<i>- Don't worry about me.
- Come on!</i>

556
00:51:53.480 --> 00:51:55.550
<i>Get down!</i>

557
00:51:55.680 --> 00:51:57.910
Uh. where am I?
Oh!

558
00:51:59.800 --> 00:52:01.756
Rool. you fool.
get out of the road!

559
00:52:17.600 --> 00:52:20.034
<i>- Ah. Franjean!
- You better clear out. Willow.</i>

560
00:52:20.160 --> 00:52:21.513
Before those troops come back.

561
00:52:21.640 --> 00:52:24.871
- Ah. my head!
- We don't need him. Elora.

562
00:52:33.000 --> 00:52:34.956
<i>Madmartigan. wait!</i>

563
00:52:35.080 --> 00:52:38.231
Go home. Willow!
It's a dangerous world.

564
00:52:38.360 --> 00:52:40.191
Yeah. and that's why
we need your help.

565
00:52:40.320 --> 00:52:43.357
My help?
What do you need my help for?

566
00:52:43.480 --> 00:52:45.471
You're a sorcerer!

567
00:52:45.600 --> 00:52:48.672
You're a great warrior.
and a swordsman.

568
00:52:48.800 --> 00:52:51.473
And you're ten times
bigger than I am. stupid!

569
00:52:51.600 --> 00:52:54.717
Are you trying to make my life
more difficult than it already is?

570
00:52:57.880 --> 00:53:02.556
<i>Hurry! Big dogs!</i>

571
00:53:02.680 --> 00:53:06.673
Look. I'm sorry I got angry.

572
00:53:06.800 --> 00:53:08.631
We wouldn't have
escaped without you.

573
00:53:22.280 --> 00:53:24.953
Well. don't expect me
to help you again.

574
00:53:26.400 --> 00:53:29.870
Good! Then we go that way!
To the lake!

575
00:53:30.920 --> 00:53:33.878
That way.

576
00:53:34.000 --> 00:53:37.436
<i>You are drunk. and when
you are drunk. you forget that...</i>

577
00:53:37.560 --> 00:53:39.357
- I am in charge!
- You are in charge.

578
00:53:39.480 --> 00:53:41.516
<i>Fine.
Then which way do we go?</i>

579
00:53:41.640 --> 00:53:43.551
That way!

580
00:53:46.520 --> 00:53:50.798
Oh. no!
That's the way I'm going.

581
00:53:50.920 --> 00:53:53.753
<i>All right. all right.
You can follow me as far as the lake.</i>

582
00:53:53.880 --> 00:53:55.916
But that's it!

583
00:53:56.040 --> 00:53:59.589
- You're not going south. are you?
- No. just as far as the lake.

584
00:53:59.720 --> 00:54:04.635
Good. Mumbo. Jumbo. I am hungry.
Go and get me some eggs or something.

585
00:54:04.760 --> 00:54:07.194
- We are not afraid of you!
- Now!

586
00:54:13.720 --> 00:54:18.111
Kael. have you found the child?

587
00:54:18.240 --> 00:54:19.912
The search goes on. my queen.

588
00:54:20.960 --> 00:54:22.871
Why. with my powers.

589
00:54:23.000 --> 00:54:25.992
with the strength
of my great army.

590
00:54:26.120 --> 00:54:29.351
can you not find
one little child?

591
00:54:29.480 --> 00:54:31.675
We look even now.
It won't be long.

592
00:54:31.800 --> 00:54:34.951
Find the child.
Find the child!

593
00:54:35.080 --> 00:54:37.548
Time is running out.

594
00:54:44.800 --> 00:54:47.439
- Good night.
- She is kinda cute.

595
00:54:49.120 --> 00:54:50.792
When she's quiet.

596
00:54:52.160 --> 00:54:53.957
She's really a princess.

597
00:54:54.080 --> 00:54:57.914
Really?
And you're a great sorcerer.

598
00:54:58.040 --> 00:54:59.792
And I'm the king of Kashmir.

599
00:54:59.920 --> 00:55:03.515
Go to sleep. Willow.

600
00:55:03.640 --> 00:55:05.995
Good night. Madmartigan.

601
00:55:06.120 --> 00:55:08.918
Rats! Big rats! Rats!

602
00:55:09.040 --> 00:55:12.191
Uh- Uh! Oh!
Rats! Ra-

603
00:55:12.320 --> 00:55:16.916
Oh. Rool. you and that
stupid rat dream! Ha!

604
00:55:25.440 --> 00:55:28.034
<i>Tuatha...</i>

605
00:55:28.160 --> 00:55:30.151
<i>Lawkathok...</i>

606
00:55:30.280 --> 00:55:32.077
<i>Tuatha!</i>

607
00:55:32.200 --> 00:55:34.794
Huh?
Willow?

608
00:55:35.840 --> 00:55:37.876
<i>Willow?</i>

609
00:55:39.600 --> 00:55:41.875
Oh.
There you are.

610
00:55:42.000 --> 00:55:43.831
Madmartigan!

611
00:55:43.960 --> 00:55:47.111
'Night. Willow.

612
00:55:58.760 --> 00:56:00.637
This way! This way!

613
00:56:12.000 --> 00:56:13.797
What are you doing?

614
00:56:13.920 --> 00:56:16.150
I found some black root.
She loves it!

615
00:56:16.280 --> 00:56:19.033
Black root? I am
the father of two children.

616
00:56:19.160 --> 00:56:21.037
and you never. ever
give a baby black root.

617
00:56:21.160 --> 00:56:24.152
Well. my mother
raised us on black root.

618
00:56:24.280 --> 00:56:26.669
It's good for ya!
It puts hair on your chest.

619
00:56:26.800 --> 00:56:29.360
- Doesn't it. Sticks?
- Her name is not Sticks.

620
00:56:29.480 --> 00:56:32.233
She's Elora Danan.
the future empress of Tir Asleen.

621
00:56:32.360 --> 00:56:34.555
And the last thing she's gonna
want is a hairy chest!

622
00:56:38.600 --> 00:56:40.477
Did you see what he did?

623
00:56:40.600 --> 00:56:43.717
He stole our black root. I'll get
some more. Don't worry about it.

624
00:56:48.400 --> 00:56:51.551
There it is! The island!

625
00:56:53.720 --> 00:56:55.517
We made it.

626
00:56:55.640 --> 00:56:59.952
<i>We have led you to
the island of the sorceress Fin Raziel.</i>

627
00:57:00.080 --> 00:57:04.119
- We'll get a boat in that village.
- A big boat.

628
00:57:21.480 --> 00:57:23.357
Well. looks like
I got you here.

629
00:57:23.480 --> 00:57:25.755
<i>You!
What did you do?</i>

630
00:57:25.880 --> 00:57:28.758
All you did was hang around
and eat our eggs! Huh?

631
00:57:28.880 --> 00:57:30.711
I found a boat.
We're all set.

632
00:57:30.840 --> 00:57:34.549
Good. Take these two lizards
out and drown them.

633
00:57:34.680 --> 00:57:37.797
<i>- Who are you calling lizards?
- Heh? Heh?</i>

634
00:57:39.880 --> 00:57:42.394
<i>Your mother was a lizard!</i>

635
00:57:45.320 --> 00:57:47.675
Goodbye. Sticks.

636
00:57:50.280 --> 00:57:52.999
If you really are a princess.

637
00:57:53.120 --> 00:57:55.953
take care of him.

638
00:58:02.120 --> 00:58:05.192
- Madmartigan!
- What?

639
00:58:05.320 --> 00:58:07.117
Thanks.

640
00:58:16.280 --> 00:58:18.635
Hey! Aah!

641
00:58:18.760 --> 00:58:21.911
<i>- Keep walkin'. hero!
- Don't even turn around!</i>

642
00:58:23.120 --> 00:58:25.953
It's all right. Elora.

643
00:58:26.080 --> 00:58:28.355
<i>Go to sleep.</i>

644
00:58:28.480 --> 00:58:32.234
Nobody'll find you here. I'll be back
with Fin Raziel very soon.

645
00:58:32.360 --> 00:58:35.511
We will guard her
with our meagre lives.

646
00:59:02.720 --> 00:59:05.359
Raziel!

647
00:59:05.480 --> 00:59:09.109
Fin Raziel!
I have to talk to you. please!

648
00:59:12.920 --> 00:59:15.354
Raziel!

